{
  "title": "The Prohibition Era (1920–1933)",
  "sections": [
    {
      "id": "overview",
      "heading": "The Prohibition Era (1920–1933)",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Prohibition was a period in the United States during which the production, sale, and transportation of alcoholic beverages were illegal."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Rather than eliminating drinking, it reshaped cocktail culture in dramatic ways."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Bars did not disappear — they went underground."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "speakeasies",
      "heading": "Speakeasies: The Hidden Bars",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Illegal bars, known as speakeasies, flourished in cities."
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Characteristics:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Hidden entrances and secret passwords",
            "Poor lighting and compact spaces",
            "Music, dancing, and social mixing",
            "Alcohol served discreetly and quickly"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Cocktails became a way to mask low-quality alcohol rather than showcase fine spirits."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "poor-quality-spirits",
      "heading": "The Rise of Poor-Quality Spirits",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "With legal distillation banned, alcohol was often:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Smuggled (bootlegged)",
            "Illegally distilled (bathtub gin)",
            "Inconsistent in quality and strength"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "To make these spirits drinkable, bartenders relied on:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Citrus juice",
            "Sugar and honey",
            "Strong flavors and spices"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "This led directly to the popularity of sweet and sour cocktails."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "cocktail-changes",
      "heading": "How Cocktails Changed",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "During Prohibition:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Cocktails became stronger in flavor",
            "Sweeteners were heavily used",
            "Fresh citrus became essential",
            "Presentation mattered less than drinkability"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Many cocktails from this era are bold, acidic, and sweet by design."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "famous-cocktails",
      "heading": "Famous Prohibition-Era Cocktails",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Several iconic cocktails gained popularity during this period:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Gin-based sours",
            "Rum cocktails influenced by Caribbean imports",
            "Champagne cocktails for disguise and luxury",
            "Simple highballs for fast service"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "These drinks prioritized speed, concealment, and flavor masking."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "bartending-impact",
      "heading": "Impact on Bartending Culture",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Prohibition had long-term effects:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Many skilled bartenders emigrated to Europe and Cuba",
            "Cocktail knowledge spread internationally",
            "American bartending standards declined temporarily",
            "Recipes became inconsistent and undocumented"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "After Prohibition ended, much traditional knowledge had to be rediscovered."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "legacy",
      "heading": "The Legacy of Prohibition",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Prohibition permanently shaped modern cocktails by:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Establishing citrus-driven cocktail structures",
            "Encouraging innovation under restriction",
            "Creating mystique around bar culture",
            "Influencing bar aesthetics still used today"
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Modern speakeasy-style bars are directly inspired by this era."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "why-it-matters",
      "heading": "Why This Matters Today",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "text": "Understanding Prohibition helps bartenders:"
        },
        {
          "type": "list",
          "items": [
            "Understand why some cocktails are sweet or citrus-heavy",
            "Respect historical context behind recipes",
            "Explain cocktail stories to guests",
            "Avoid repeating past mistakes in balance and quality"
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
